# Financial Transactions API

## Overview
Manage user deposits and withdrawals.

## Endpoints

GET    /api/FinancialTransactions  
    List all financial transactions.  
    - Returns: Array of transaction objects.

GET    /api/FinancialTransactions/user/{userId}  
    List all transactions for a specific user.  
    - Path parameter: userId (int) â€” User identifier.  
    - Returns: Array of transaction objects.

POST   /api/FinancialTransactions  
    Create a new financial transaction (deposit or withdrawal).  
    - Request body: Transaction object (UserID, CashAmount, TransactionType).  
    - Returns: Created transaction object.

## Error Responses

- 400: Invalid transaction data (e.g., negative amount, missing fields).
- 401: Unauthorized.
- 404: User not found.
- 422: Insufficient balance for withdrawal.
- 500: Server error.

